cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

This paper is about optimizing hyper-parameters for neural machine translation using deep learning neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of GPUs and FPGAs for training, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
